				<div class='case-content large-12 columns'>
					<section id='overview'>
						<div class="large-10 large-centered columns">
							<h3>Shop Smarter</h3>
							<p>Why does a trip to Safeway feel like a necessary evil? Stores are maze-like, items are elusive or forgotten, and waiting to check out is a pain. SmartCart tackled two major pain points in the grocery shopping experience: finding items and checking out.  </p>
						</div>

						<div class='video-wrapper center'>
							<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7QvktffdVp4" frameborder="0" width="560" height="200" allowfullscreen></iframe>
						</div>

					</section>

					<section id='prototyping'>
						<div class="large-10 large-centered columns">
							<h3>Prototyping</h3>
							<p>Needfinding in this project began with talking with shoppers about supermarket frustrations, following their shopping habits, and talking with employees about self-checkout hassles and inefficiencies. After considering a number of prototypes, <a href='http://smartcart247.weebly.com/prototyping.html'>from Kinect to Leap Motion to capacitive sensing handlebars</a>, we decided on a tablet app. 
							</p>
						</div>

						<figure>
							<img src='images/smartcart/007.png' />
							<figcaption>initial mockup of adding items (Photoshop)</figcaption>
						</figure>
					</section>

					<section id='user-testing'>
						<div class="large-10 large-centered columns">
							<h3>User Testing</h3>
							<p> For user testing, we highlighted two main goals: <em>does SmartCart help users find what they need in grocery stores more efficiently?</em> and <em>does SmartCart make shopping less frustrating?</em> We invited participants to <a href='http://smartcart247.weebly.com/user-testing.html'>interact with SmartCart as if they were shopping regularly</a>. From tests, several interface issues were highlighted, but most prominent was the ambiguity found in checking out. Shoppers were reminded of an online experience, instead of a physical store. We added additional dialogues and more obvious actions to simplify the checkout process. </p>
						</div>

						<figure>
							<img src='images/smartcart/smartcartHiDef.jpg'>
							<figcaption>high-fidelity mockup of list &amp; map view</figcaption>
						</figure>

						<div class="large-10 large-centered columns">
							<p>Users highlighted a number of problems, ranging from cryptic system statuses to mismatches between the system and the real world. The next iteration included a number of features, such as <a href='http://smartcart247.weebly.com/functional-2.html'>adding autocomplete, resolving ambiguous items, and detailing checkout instructions</a>. Perhaps the biggest issue shoppers found was how difficult it was to use the SmartCart in coordination with a physical cart. The tablet seemed more like a peripheral accessory than an integrated component, so we designed a hardware enclosure to ease use and accessibility of the touchscreen.</p>
						</div>

						<figure>
							<img src='images/smartcart/test2.jpg'>
